<paragraph blockId="12.[178,1087,360,499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
R e m a r k s: the authors regard this as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[784,969,360,382]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">
<emphasis box="[784,969,360,382]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia pontica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[178,438,389,411]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcaucasica">
<emphasis box="[178,438,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia transcaucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter taxon is here considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LEDERER" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolenta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia sanguinolenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<emphasis box="[392,725,418,440]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LEDERER" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[392,565,418,440]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolenta">B. sanguinolenta</taxonomicName>
transcaucasica
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[732,826,419,440]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<emphasis box="[878,1086,419,440]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[878,983,419,440]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">B. pontica</taxonomicName>
turcmena
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[178,269,448,469]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">stat. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were sampled on the same locality. 
<emphasis box="[664,878,449,470]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[664,772,449,470]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">B. pontica</taxonomicName>
turcmena
</emphasis>
was only observed south of 
<collectingRegion box="[266,311,478,499]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Van</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
